Zulfiqar Ali (born 1965) is former mayor of Rochdale, in the north west of England. He was born in Bradford.  He took office in 2010.Ali is the chairman of Reach BCS, Rochdale, Greater Manchester. 
In 2008, he was awarded the Queen's Award for Enterprise Promotion.

response: Zulfiqar Ali (born 1947, Mombasa, Kenya) was a right-handed cricket bowler who played three ODIs for East Africa. In his third match, against England, he took three wickets for 63 runs, the best figures by any East African bowler.
